QUE: Explain the difference between static and instance methods.
ANS: 
	1. Static Method:
			class Demo {
		    static void show() {
		        System.out.println("Static method");
		    }
		}
		
		a. Belongs to the class.
		b. Can be called using class name.
		c. Cannot access instance variables directly.
		d. Loaded once when the class is loaded.
		e. Called after initialization and before the main class.
		
		
	2. Instance Method:
			class Demo {
		     void show() {
		        System.out.println("Instance method");
		    }
		}
		
		a. Belongs to an object.
		b. Called using object reference
		c. Can access both instance and static variables